pull_request.title: Shared lib testing update
pull_request.body:
This PR adds
- OSX testing (in CircleCI)
- Adds `SKIP_TESTS` features for more resource-sensitive CI testing
- Workaround for CCI CPU feature detection problems
- Workaround for OSX SIP (DY)LD_LIBRARY_PATH env var removal when testing shared libs

##### Checklist
- [na] documentation is added or updated
- [x] tests are added or updated

pull_request.title: Testing macOS release build.
pull_request.body:
I basically kept the CPU extension detection code as is, so that the `USE_*_INSTRUCTIONS` variables are still set the same way, but removed the part adding individual flags and used `march=native` instead. 

The macOS release build passes on CircleCI with this. I'm a bit surprised it works, but I think we can make do with this until we have the `cpu_features` library.
